--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
WHO MADE LUMEN?
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Lumen Colors was created by aizy_lazy, a Discord user and developer who got tired
of the same problem: setting up color roles in servers was a hassle.

Whether it was manually creating dozens of roles, copying role IDs, or keeping
reaction menus in sync, managing color roles was time-consuming and error-prone.
So he built Lumen—a bot that does the heavy lifting and lets server members pick
their color with a single reaction.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
WHY LUMEN EXISTS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  • To make color roles easy
    No more creating every shade by hand or pasting role IDs. Run a short setup
    wizard, and Lumen creates the roles and reaction menus for you.

  • To stay flexible
    You choose the channel, how many shades (Basic, Standard, or Full), optional
    role restrictions (required role / restricted role), and whether to use
    custom banners or none. You can change most of this later in the Dashboard.

  • To keep things simple for users
    Server members just react with an emoji to get or change their color role.
    One reaction per family; no complicated commands.

  • To give server staff control
    Rename or recolor roles in Server Settings → Roles anytime; Lumen keeps
    working. Use the Dashboard to edit emojis, banners, embed colors, and who
    can use color roles.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
WHAT'S IN A NAME?
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

"Lumen" means light—and color is all about light. The bot helps servers shine
with simple, customizable color roles.

